I rarely post a review, but this was such an atrocious experience i felt the need to vent. We were seated quickly and the menu truly looked fantastic. Then our waiter approached. He was smug, uninterested in us, and just not deserving to be in in the service industry. He was unable to make any recomondations on the menu. 2 of 4 people ordered fish. At the end of ordering the waiter rudely told us that the fish will come last after the pasta. I asked him to see if they could come together. His response was, “we cant do that”, i asked “why not”, he answered “the kitchen doesnt work that way because the fish takes longer to cook”. I then suggested for him to have the fish put on the grill earlier than the pasta so it would all cone together”. His reponse, “i’m not sure it can be done” as he walked away. The sushi roll we ordered was far less tasty than the menue suggested. I asked waiter if it was the correct roll amd he said yes without even looming at it. 20 minutes later the waiter comes back and tells us they are out of the bronzino (the 2 fish dishes that were ordered). We ordered, the food came (quickly and together) and we ate. I made it two bites into my pasta “fromage” which tasted like bad alfredo. No flavor amd a major disappointment. The waiter didnt notice my plate was untouched nor did he ask. We had to summon bus boys and waiters to picl up dishes as they puled up. No one refilled our water despite our requests. Our chocolate soufflé was basically a warm pudding over chocolate cake prepared in a glass cup. Clearly a micrvowaved concoction to heat up, not a standard soufflé. Total bill was $200 for 2 pastas, 2 salads, 2 sushi rolls, fries, a pizza and a dessert; absolutely not worth it. Props to the menu designer for making the food sound more flavorful than it is. This restaraunt need a good overhaul or what good food and good service means. I heard they were hosting their employee appreciate dinner in the back last night. Glad they did it at my expense.

Thanks Moe Molcho! - Here's some advice. If a restaurant is going to be closing in 60-30 minutes and you wanna play a cards against humanity game with your friends at the table that could take 2-3 hours to get through on a Wednesday evening; then, just don't go and host at your place. Take other people into consideration. I didn't rush you through your meal. Your food came as you ordered it. You order the food and it comes to the table ( that's how that works ). I waited your table to the end properly and politely. I didn't take your plate that you were still eating off of man. Be honest. That plate had one half piece of greens on it no bigger than 1 inch with your fork sitting in the middle of your plate in the leftover sauce and you hadn't touched it in 10 minutes. If you weren't done eating it then what were you going to do with it? Save it for a museum? Were you going to pull your soiled fork out of the sauce and wipe it off to get the last bite? Come on man. Be honest. I asked if you wanted anything else, you guys said no, I ran you the check, paid you out and I left home to study for my MATH FINAL. Now I'm feeling considerably better about my math test but I'm out a job that I really loved in the middle of finals week because you're an inconsiderate and rude customer who finds it appropriate to leave a one star review to an establishment and a server that never did anything wrong to you. During Hanukkah too! You're Jewish. I saw your kippahs. You think that's a proper way to act towards other people? Be they your server or not? I know I'm goyim but sheesh man you need to open your eyes. Judging by the other reviews you've left restaurants on your Google profile it almost seems you could make a good living with a part time job of slandering people for no good reason. Now instead of using my day off tomorrow to study more so I know I'll pass I have to leave that behind and go out to find another job to support myself. Then, not to mention, the family issues I'm going through right now. Wow. Sorry I don't have much respect for people who cannot respect others. _('_')_/ Thanks for being you buddy! Shout out to your great considerate friends too! Real classy and respectful folks. Good on you! Good on you brother!

The service was good. Our waiter was reliable and showed up at the appropriate times. My main complaints are about the food. I ordered the pan-seared salmon, which I believe costs $38. For that price, I thought it would be heavenly, but I was utterly disappointed. The dish was served on a gloomy black plate. The fish and rice were crammed into one third of the plate whereas the yogurt sauce occupied the rest. The vegetables placed on top of the salmon, seemingly as a garnish, were textureless, flavorless, and lacked vibrancy. As for the taste of the dish, the rice and yogurt sauce were of acceptable quality. The salmon, however, tasted fairly bland. It was surprisingly textureless considering that it was supposed to be seared – I wouldn't be surprised if it was actually baked. I craved savoriness but that desire couldn't be sated with the bland salmon and the mildly tangy yogurt sauce. Our desserts were even worse than the salmon. I assume they make the desserts in-house because it was undercooked and we were able to taste the beaten egg whites. With that said, they have solid pizza and fries, so I'll give them two stars for that.

Big thank you to Urbana! Excellent food, ambiance and service. Everything you could ask for and more. Usually motse Shabbat restaurants are not really operating on all cylinders or at least that is how it feels oftentimes... but they never let us see them sweat tonight! We showed up, myself, my husband and 5 kids varying in age from 19 to 9 and not only did they get us a great table in a cozy nook but the wait was only like 15 minutes on a very busy Saturday night. They were very accommodating with our various requests even though they warned us it would mean that we would have to forgive the presentation, (which was still quite beautiful despite our various requests). The food was delicious, perfectly executed and really imaginative and no one left with out a smile on their face. Thank you Dimitri and to the kind, patient, professional manager! You guys made our night! Really a class act! I have to say even though we ordered every app and every dessert I failed to take pictures of everything because we were so busy enjoying our selves.  ** Update:  Once again a big shout out to Urbana, Sam took great care of us and the food was beyond! We had a lot of our favorites from last time which were consistent and delicious. 😋 We also decided to try the Polenta which was a revelation on polenta, I have made it and eaten it many times but this is a whole new take and a delectable one at that. It was creamy, almost soupy, with a fresh corn flavor and the flavor of Parmesan and fresh cream was divine, that with the chewy, juicy mushrooms came together in a really sumptuous dish. We also decided to try the Ocean Crudo Tostada which was the ultimate bite, it was balanced, creamy, crunchy, it hit on all the tastes you want, umami, sweet, salty, sour... like I said the ultimate bite. I was dining with someone who had never had raw fish and Sam our waitress recommended this, and she was so spot on, my friend tried raw fish for the first time and loved it! We also tried a couple of new desserts the creme brûlée and the pink merengue...They have the best creme brûlée I have ever had (better than my own I'm sad to say) and the pink merengue dessert was unexpected and divine, the hazelnut chocolate sauce is like liquid ferro rocher... Thank you Urbana for a great night!
